theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure A := by
  -- We establish the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
    have h₁ : (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h₁
  · -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
    -- Since `A` is open and contained in `closure A`, it is also contained in the interior.
    have h₂ : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_maximal (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A) hA
    -- Taking closures yields the desired inclusion.
    exact closure_mono h₂
